m] path1 [path2 ...]\nGiven a list  of paths, finds and returns a list of valid addons paths.\nWith -m flag, will return a list of modules names instead.", "!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [{"name": "vxci.get_addons.is_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["return False if the path doesn't contain an odoo module, and the full\npath to the module manifest otherwise"]}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.find_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "paths", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Find module in paths\n\\:param module: String with name of module to find in paths.\n\\:param paths: List of strings with paths to search.\n\\:return: String with full path of manifest file found\n"]}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.is_installable_module", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["return False if the path doesn't contain an installable odoo module,\nand the full path to the module manifest otherwise"]}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.get_modules", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.is_addons", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.get_addons", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.get_depends", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "addons_path_list", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "modules_list", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get recursive depends from addons_paths and modules list\n\\:param modules_list: List of strings with name of modules\n\\:param addons_path_list: List of strings with path of modules\n\\:return set: Unsorted set of recursive dependencies of modules\n"]}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.get_module_list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.get_modules2test", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "folder", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "include", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "exclude", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.join_prefix_suffix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "items", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "prefix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "suffix", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Use \"str.join\" but forcing a prefix even for the first item.\n\ne.g.\nitems = [\"module1\", \"module2\", \"module3\"]\nprefix = \"/\"\nsuffix = \",\"\nResult = \"/module1,/module2,/module3\"\n\nUsing the \"str.join\" method for the same input:\n',/'.join(items)\nthe output is 'module1,/module2,/module3'\nNotice the prefix for first item is missed.\nSo, it needs to be inserted (only if the result is not empty).\n\nitems = [\"\"]\nResult: \"\"\n\nThe default suffix is \",\" if it is not defined"]}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.get_tags", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "modules", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tags", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Transform modules to /tag_module items.\n\nIf the \"tags\" variable is not defined so all the modules will be the tags.\nmodules = [\"module1\", \"module2\", \"module3\"]\ntags = None\nResult: \"/module1,/module2,/module3\"\n\nIf the \"tags\" variable has an item with the string \"ALL\"\nSo, the tags related to modules will be appended.\nmodules = [\"module1\", \"module2\", \"module3\"]\ntags = \"ALL,tag1\"\nResult = \"/module1,/module2,/module3,tag1\"\n\nNotice the tags do not need extra prefixes but modules.\n\nif the \"tags\" variable has an item it will be used without /tag_module items.\nmodules = [\"module1\", \"module2\", \"module3\"]\ntags = \"-tag1,tag2\"\nResult: \"-tag1,tag2\"\n\nif the \"tags\" variable is empty so all the /tag_module will be append."]}], "variables": [{"name": "vxci.get_addons.ifilter", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.imap", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.MANIFEST_FILES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.modules", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags_str", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags_str", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags_str", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.get_addons.tags_str", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "vxci.checkers.read_varsfile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers.get_file_values", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers.check_varsfile_syntax", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers.check_varsfile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers.check_required_envars", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers.check_envars", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vxci.checkers.check_mainapp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns